¶ 43. 'Tis not long ſince one of us, had the Honour to be called upon, to give an Opinion upon an important Point before this Houſe; what Influence that Service may have had upon the Cauſe of the preſent Complaint, is hard for us to determine; but our Hope is, that our Country, whoſe Good we have always ſincerely conſulted;
Here Mr. Smith took Notice, that that Opinion was demanded and given upon his Sincerity and Honour.
                and as we have been called upon, have publickly ſerved, will not deny us its Protection, nor ſuffer us to be cruſhed for our faithful Adherence to its Intereſts and honeſt Diſcharge of our Duty.
